    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-01-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-01-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="31" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d31">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Harvey</persName>,
                                    United Slates minister, to Mr. <persName type="to">Seward</persName>, Secretary of State.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Lisbon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-01-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 30, 1864</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Duke de Loulé addressed me a
                                fourth note, (of which a copy in translation is inclosed,)
                                yesterday, on the subject of my recent representation, <pb facs="0097" n="77" xml:id="pg_77"/> and from which it appears
                                that the entire authority of every department of His Majesty’s
                                government has now been seriously and energetically invoked to
                                prevent rebel cruisers from arming or equipping in the island ports
                                of this kingdom.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JAMES E. HARVEY.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
